<TEXT>
the us supreme court granted a 
temporary stay of execution wednesday night for a 28yearold 
murderer who was scheduled to die by injection for a fatal 
convenience story holdup that netted 24 
warren bridges execution scheduled for after 1 am edt 
thursday was stayed by the full court spokeswoman toni house said 
the court granted the temporary stay pending a timely filing of 
a request for a full review of the case by the court she said 
a federal district judge in galveston had refused to stay 
bridges execution for for the 1980 shooting of walter rose 62 in 
a convenience store robbery bridges lawyer then took his case to 
the 5th us circuit court of appeals 
bridge would have been the 102nd inmate executed nationally and 
the 28th in texas since the us supreme court ruling in 1976 
allowing states to resume the use of the death penalty 
galveston attorney anthony griffin contended in his appeal that 
during the punishment phase of bridges murder trial jurors were 
not allowed to consider mitigating circumstances or facts that 
might have led them to settle on a lesser punishment 
griffin cited arguments used in an appeal filed on behalf of 
texas death row inmate johnny penry whose case the us supreme 
court has agreed to hear 
after his arrest for the shooting bridge escaped briefly from 
the galveston county jail by knocking out a hole in the jail wall 
he was captured 19 hours later hitchhiking along a freeway 
rose was shot four times with a 38caliber pistol as bridge and 
his codefendant robert joseph costa robbed the convenience store 
of 24 on feb 10 1980 rose died of his wounds on feb 24 1980 
four days after bridge and costa were arrested 
costa was convicted of aggravated robbery and sentenced to 13 
years in prison he was released under mandatory supervision in 
october 1986 after serving five years and eight months in prison 
bridge a native of fauquier county va said he was in trouble 
since he was 8 he grew up in albany ga and before moving to 
texas he served 13 months of a 15year prison term for burglary in 
georgia 
bridge said in a recent interview that he was sorry rose died 
but complained his life on death row was worse than the shooting 
victims fate 
i sit here on death row for 7 years and think about dying 
and i believe mr rose got a better deal he said i keep 
wishing they would hurry up and do something i tell you this 
place will drive you crazy 
during his time on death row bridge was implicated in the 
bombing of another inmates cell and the nonfatal stabbing of a 
second inmate in incidents blamed on prison gang warfare bridge 
also was linked to membership in the aryan brotherhood a white 
supremacist prison gang 
im not affiliated he said in the interview im friends 
with everybody and now ive got a black attorney its a touchy 
subject 
</TEXT>
