<TEXT>
facts and figures on the britishcontrolled cayman islands 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
the geography the three islands grand cayman the largest 
little cayman and cayman brac cover 100 square miles they are 
located in the caribbean sea about 200 miles northwest of jamaica 
the islands flat terrain is surrounded by clear waters and has 
a tropical climate with a hurricane season between july and 
november 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
the people the population of nearly 23000 is mostly 
protestant and roman catholic and is of mixed european and black 
african descent english is the countrys official language 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
the economy the islands big moneyearners are financial 
services and tourism the economy also benefits from shipbuilding 
turtle and shark fishing coconut farming and textile and 
automobile production the 1987 per capita income was 9000 in 
1988 the islands could accomodate more than 5000 tourists at a 
time and at least 480792 people visited the island in 1987 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
history the cayman islands were discovered by christopher 
columbus in 1503 and came under british control in 1670 they 
became a colony in 1959 and were administered by jamaica until a 
governor was appointed in 1972 the legislature includes the 
governor three officials and 12 elected members 
</TEXT>
