<TEXT>
kroger co the nations largest grocery 
chain has proposed a 38 billion restructuring plan to shield 
itself against any hostile takeover bids 
the cincinnatibased company said tuesday it was considering a 
plan that would make kroger an unattractive takeover target by 
raising its stock price loading it up with new debt placing 20 
percent of its shares under control of its employees and selling 
off parts of the company 
the proposal followed news that the haft family of maryland 
received federal antitrust clearance to acquire kroger stock and 
pushed kroger shares sharply higher 
kroger stock soared by 1175 a share to 5125 in heavy trading 
tuesday on the new york stock exchange 
under the restructuring shareholders would get a onetime cash 
dividend of 40 per share and would receive longterm bonds worth 
another 8 a share while retaining their kroger common stock 
based on its 7857 million common shares outstanding it would 
cost about 315 billion to pay the dividends kroger also would 
have to borrow another 630 million to cover the bonds 
by continuing as an independent company the interests of our 
employees customers and the communities in which we operate would 
also be protected said kroger chairman lyle everingham 
krogers directors will meet in the very near future to vote 
on the plan company representative paul bernish said 
directors met in emergency session friday to prepare the 
protection plan only hours after the federal trade commission told 
the hafts they could buy kroger stock without violating antitrust 
laws 
the hafts have launched a number of major raids against grocery 
companies and other retailers including unsuccessful but 
profitable hostile bids for safeway supermarkets general and stop 
n shop it was not known how much kroger stock the hafts own 
although they must disclose when they acquire 5 percent or more of 
the companys outstanding shares 
the ftc clearance was the first official sign of the hafts 
interest in kroger although kroger stock has has traded heavily 
over the past five months amid rumors the hafts and other potential 
acquirers were interested in the company representatives of the 
hafts declined to comment 
kroger reported sales of almost 18 billion in 1987 it operates 
1317 supermarkets nationwide as well as 900 convenience stores 
and employs 170000 people 
kroger said it will repay the debt incurred in the restructuring 
using cash flow from operations reducing expenses and selling 
assets in a 1986 restructuring kroger sold its chain of superx 
retail drugstores and kroger has worked since july to sell off its 
unprofitable chain of florida choice supermarkets and liquor stores 
in florida 
