deficit in the current account the broadest measure of us trade 
shrank to 333 billion in the second quarter a 98 percent 
improvement from a first quarter imbalance of 369 billion 
it was the biggest quarterly improvement since a 201 percent 
drop in the final three months of last year the current account 
covers trade in merchandise as well as trade in services which 
