and to replace three of the six directors with its own nominees 
our decision is based on the firm conviction that direction is 
needed to ensure the boards compliance with the collective will of 
the companys shareholders the dissident group said in a letter 
to zeniths board 
spokesman john taylor said zenith officials had not seen a copy 
of the lawsuit so it is inappropriate to comment 
zenith the last remaining us television manufacturer has 
been fighting a losing battle against lowpriced imported 
televisions 
despite the success of its highly regarded computers zenith 
suffered multimilliondollar losses for the past three years 
including a loss of 191 million last year on sales of 236 
billion 
the companys stock gained 12 cents wednesday in composite 
trading on the new york stock exchange closing at 2175 
peter harkins general counsel for brookhurst partners said in 
a telephone interview that the group would seek written consents 
from shareholders to undertake its plan 
he said brookhurst had filed a lawsuit in us district court in 
delaware challenging a provision in zeniths articles of 
incorporation that requires the unanimous consent of all 
stockholders for an action initiated by written consent to be 
effective 
brookhurst claims the provision violates delaware laws 
guaranteeing the right of stockholders to take action by written 
consent he said zenith is incorporated in delaware 
zenith posted a profit of 400000 or 1 cent a share on sales 
of 5741 million in the first quarter of 1988 but had a second 
quarter loss of 121 million 
zenith chairman jerry k pearlman has said repeatedly since 
april that the board was exploring all options for returning 
the company to profitability including selling its 
televisionmaking consumer electronics unit 
but brookhurst formed by herbert b abelow and nicholas l 
ihasz specifically to acquire zenith stock said it no longer could 
tolerate the boards apparent inaction or its strategy of cutting 
costs while waiting for television prices to stablilize 
in our view this can lead only to increased debt lower 
earnings inadequate cash flow and more serious financial 
difficulties the partnership said in its letter 
other major shareowners have expressed to us their agreement 
with our views and frustration with the board of directors 
continuing failure to enhance share value 
abelow ihasz and paul street would be the three brookhurst 
nominees to zeniths board harkins said 
the partnership proposes to retain directors john h johnson 
wilbur h gantz and frederick g jaicks none of whom work for 
zenith and to dump pearlman harry b beckner sidney davidson g 
ralph gurthrie robert b hansen john w madigan and arthur w 
schultz harkins said 
