<TEXT>
general electric capital corp will get 15 
percent of the stock in struggling new world entertainment corp in 
return for an 80 million loan aimed at helping the movie and 
television company service its heavy longterm debt the companies 
announced wednesday 
the loan which new world intends to repay with proceeds from 
the planned sale of its marvel entertainment group allowed the 
company to redeem 1415 million in longterm debt the new 80 
million loan brings to 115 million the credit from stamford 
connbased ge capital to new world 
the debt restructuring is a cornerstone of the turnaround for 
new world said harry evans sloan cochairman 
the latest debt transaction combined with two similar moves 
earlier this year reduced new worlds longterm debt from 285 
million to 55 million interest costs which had been crippling 
new world will be cut from more than 33 million a year to about 
6 million a year sloan said 
marvel which makes comic books such as spiderman and the 
incredible hulk and cartoons has attracted numerous bidders but 
a sale agreement has not been reached sloan said 
new world lost 79 million in the first quarter of this year 
but is banking on the debt swap and potential earnings from new tv 
shows and movies including crime story and the wonder 
years a new show which won an emmy award 
the companys most recent movies 18 again dead heat 
and wrong guys did not do well at the box office 
